      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUST A NUISANCE (4) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 1.75 lengths at this track in a handy 34.73 beating Cool Blue You. Has good early speed so he should be prominent despite the squeeze draw. Looks the one to beat. CHAOTIC BOY (6) flew the lids with a fast early split and went on to clock 16.74 when a 3.5 lengths winner over 300m at Murray Bridge. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Has definite claims. AGENT TWENTY ONE (8) is worth forgiving for his last effort when fourth (31.09) at this track over 530m. Has a good record here including three wins. Has good speed and will be prominent from out wide. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. BRISTOL MOSS (1) can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
